\subsection{Error Sources and Truncation Control}
Dominant errors stem from bond truncation (finite $\chi$) and finite memory window $W$. We monitor discarded weight and nRMSE, adapting $\chi$ as needed. For moderate $W\sim \beta\log S_{\rm BH}$ and $\chi\in[64,128]$, Page-curve observables are well captured.

\section{Predictions and Falsifiability}
\label{sec:predictions}
\subsection{Analogue Hawking Platforms}
HMC predicts $O(1/S_{\rm BH})$ sidebands in $g^{(2)}(\Delta u)$ with correlation time $\tau_{\rm mem}\sim \beta \log S_{\rm BH}$ and memory frequency $\omega_{\rm mem}$ from $\Xi^R(\omega)$ poles (Eqs.~\ref{eq:kernel_schwarzian}, \ref{eq:kernel_4d}). In sonic black-hole experiments~\cite{Barcelo:2011, Steinhauer:2016}, matched-filter searches for oscillatory-exponential templates can be used. The expected SNR scales as $\epsilon \sqrt{T/\tau_{\rm mem}}$ with $\epsilon\!=\!O(1/S_{\rm BH})$. Multi-run bootstraps yield CIs and FDR-controlled p-values.

\subsection{Gravitational-Wave Ringdowns}
The retarded kernel imprints small, coherent phase modulations (soft echoes) at late times. While claims of echoes remain debated~\cite{Cardoso:2016, Abedi:2017}, HMC predicts a specific, retarded structure constrained by greybody factors and $\Xi^R$. Search templates combining standard QNMs with causal sidebands and cross-mode phase-correlation statistics, followed by multi-event stacking, can constrain $\varepsilon$ and $\tau_{\rm mem}$.

\subsection{Parameter Inference and Kernel Tomography}
Given Page-like entropies and $g^{(2)}$, regularized fits (e.g., rational approximants with KMS/FDT constraints) can reconstruct $\Xi^R(\omega)$ within model families (Schwarzian-like vs membrane-like), providing falsifiable signatures.

\subsection{When HMC Could Fail}
If no sidebands beyond systematics are found across analogue platforms, and if independent evidence disfavors island/fuzzball/nonlocal mechanisms, HMC would be challenged. Conversely, observation of high-energy firewall-like excitations would falsify P3.

\section{Discussion and Outlook}
\label{sec:discussion}
\paragraph{Scrambling (P2).} The Comb Page Theorem relies on typical scramblers. Our ablations and TN results indicate robustness at moderate depths and $\chi$. Mapping design order to gravitational dynamics remains open.

\paragraph{Microscopic 4D Kernel.} Our 4D kernel derivation is effective; canonical boundary charge quantization with retarded correlators matched to greybody factors is a promising direction.

\paragraph{Stochastic Backreaction.} Einstein–Langevin analysis suggests $S_{\rm BH}^{-1/2}$-suppressed fluctuations after averaging. A detector-level simulator within the influence-functional formalism is feasible.

\paragraph{Scalability.} The MPO/MPS implementation scales well for Page-curve observables. Future work: adaptive windows, dynamic $\chi$ control guided by discarded weight, and improved process-tensor constructions.

\paragraph{Limitations.} The finite window and $\chi$ may under-resolve subtle late-time effects, though trends are clear. Analogue and GW searches will give decisive tests.

\subsection*{Future Work}
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
\item First-principles 4D kernel via boundary charge quantization and retarded correlators with greybody matching.
\item Larger-scale TN simulations: adaptive-window process tensors, operator-space TNs, and parallelized contractions.
\item Detector-level predictions: matched-filter statistics for comb sidebands and GW soft echoes under realistic noise.
\item Relation to islands: derive island-like results from HMC dynamics and clarify regimes of (in)equivalence.
\end{itemize}

\section{Conclusion}
\label{sec:conclusion}
We proposed the Horizon Memory Comb as a unifying, dynamical resolution of black-hole information puzzles. By elevating non-Markovianity to the central organizing principle, HMC reconciles unitary evaporation with a smooth horizon. We derived postulates and kernels from edge modes, JT gravity, and the 4D membrane paradigm; the kernels are causal, gentle ($\sim 1/S_{\rm BH}$), and encode temporal nonlocality that unitarizes evaporation without violating local smoothness. We validated the framework numerically (toy, exact comb, MPO/MPS) with ablations, significance tests, K-fold CV, and complexity analysis. HMC yields concrete, falsifiable predictions for analogue platforms and gravitational-wave ringdowns, offering a coherent, scalable, and testable route toward resolving the information paradox.

\appendix

\section{Appendix A: Decoupling Bound for Quantum Combs}
\label{app:decoupling}
For early times ($d_{R_{\le n}}\ll d_{M_n}$),
\begin{equation}
\left\|\rho_{R_{\le n}} - \frac{\mathbbm{1}}{d_{R_{\le n}}}\right\|_1 \le O\!\left(\sqrt{\frac{d_{R_{\le n}}}{d_{M_n}}}\right).
\end{equation}
Post-Page, the shrinking memory plus scrambling decouples $I_n M_n$ from early radiation, transferring coherent information to $R_{\le n}$. Approximate $t$-designs with $t=\Omega(\log d_M)$ yield additive $O(\log S_{\rm BH})$ corrections~\cite{Brandao:2016}.

\section{Appendix B: Stress Tensor Estimates and Hadamard Property}
\label{app:stress_tensor}
The kernel-corrected Wightman function (from Sec.~\ref{sec:influence}) remains Hadamard after smearing~\cite{Radzikowski:1996}. Point-splitting renormalization yields $\langle T_{\mu\nu}\rangle_{\rm ren}$ bounded by $O(\kappa^4/S_{\rm BH})$ in a local free-fall frame.

\section{Appendix C: Moving Mirror Analogue with Memory}
\label{app:moving_mirror}
A moving mirror endowed with a memory kernel modifies boundary conditions. Coarse-grained spectra are thermal while higher-order correlations show structured, retarded deviations, illustrating boundary-mediated temporal nonlocality.

\section{Appendix D: Schwarzian Correlators and the Memory Kernel}
\label{app:schwarzian_appendix}
Expanding around $f(u)=u$ and integrating out the Schwarzian mode yields Eq.~\eqref{eq:kernel_schwarzian}; thermal sums and analytic continuation give the digamma structure, with overall scale fixed by $C\propto S_{\rm BH}$.

\section{Appendix E: Code Availability and Reproducibility}
\label{app:code}
A self-contained script deterministically generates all v3 datasets (toy Page curves, $g^{(2)}$ with CIs, ablation summaries with significance, exact comb outputs, MPS/MPO scaling and nRMSE curves, and K-fold CV summaries). Command-line flags control seeds, runs, and folds. If files already exist, embedded v3 datasets ensure compilation; re-running the script regenerates identical filenames deterministically.

